commit.message:
filters.decimation: support non-integer step (#4348)

Allow specifying a non-integer step to the decimation filter. This
permits keeping more than 50% of the input points.

eg: a step value of 1.6 will keep (100 / 1.6) = 62.5% of the input.

tree 4d8cc301dcf35856f1ecd196b518ac2974a51bfc

filters.decimation: support non-integer step (#4348)

Allow specifying a non-integer step to the decimation filter. This
permits keeping more than 50% of the input points.

eg: a step value of 1.6 will keep (100 / 1.6) = 62.5% of the input.
